verbose_text: A/E pathogens typically secrete 25-30 effectors, which subvert various host processes, including opsonophagocytosis, activation of nuclear factor kappaB (NF-kappaB), mitogen activated protein kinases (MAPKs), type I interferons, and cell death.
evidence: activation of nuclear factor kappaB (NF-kappaB), mitogen-activated protein kinases
